verses.text_plain: Blessed be the Lord my strength, which teacheth my hands to war, and my fingers to fight:
verses.verse_html:
1Blessed be the Lord my strength, which teacheth my hands to war, and my fingers to fight: ▼
▼ strength: Heb. rock
 , ▼
▼ to war…: Heb. to the war, etc

footnotes.body_text: ▼ to war…: Heb. to the war, etc
footnotes.body_html: ▼ to war…: Heb. to the war, etc

verses.text_plain: My goodness, and my fortress; my high tower, and my deliverer; my shield, and he in whom I trust; who subdueth my people under me.
verses.verse_html:
2My goodness, and my fortress; my high tower, and my deliverer; my shield, and he in whom I trust; who subdueth my people under me. ▼
▼ My goodness: or, My mercy

footnotes.body_html: ▼ My goodness: or, My mercy

verses.text_plain: Lord, what is man, that thou takest knowledge of him! or the son of man, that thou makest account of him!
verses.verse_html: 3Lord, what is man, that thou takest knowledge of him! or the son of man, that thou makest account of him!

verses.text_plain: Man is like to vanity: his days are as a shadow that passeth away.
verses.verse_html: 4Man is like to vanity: his days are as a shadow that passeth away.

verses.text_plain: Bow thy heavens, O Lord, and come down: touch the mountains, and they shall smoke.
verses.verse_html: 5Bow thy heavens, O Lord, and come down: touch the mountains, and they shall smoke.

verses.text_plain: Cast forth lightning, and scatter them: shoot out thine arrows, and destroy them.
verses.verse_html: 6Cast forth lightning, and scatter them: shoot out thine arrows, and destroy them.

verses.text_plain: Send thine hand from above; rid me, and deliver me out of great waters, from the hand of strange children;
verses.verse_html:
7Send thine hand from above; rid me, and deliver me out of great waters, from the hand of strange children; ▼
▼ hand from: Heb. hands from

footnotes.body_html: ▼ hand from: Heb. hands from

verses.text_plain: Whose mouth speaketh vanity, and their right hand is a right hand of falsehood.
verses.verse_html: 8Whose mouth speaketh vanity, and their right hand is a right hand of falsehood.

verses.text_plain: I will sing a new song unto thee, O God: upon a psaltery and an instrument of ten strings will I sing praises unto thee.
verses.verse_html: 9I will sing a new song unto thee, O God: upon a psaltery and an instrument of ten strings will I sing praises unto thee.

verses.text_plain: It is he that giveth salvation unto kings: who delivereth David his servant from the hurtful sword.
verses.verse_html:
10It is he that giveth salvation unto kings: who delivereth David his servant from the hurtful sword. ▼
▼ salvation: or, victory

verses.text_plain: Rid me, and deliver me from the hand of strange children, whose mouth speaketh vanity, and their right hand is a right hand of falsehood:
verses.verse_html: 11Rid me, and deliver me from the hand of strange children, whose mouth speaketh vanity, and their right hand is a right hand of falsehood:

verses.text_plain: That our sons may be as plants grown up in their youth; that our daughters may be as corner stones, polished after the similitude of a palace:
verses.verse_html:
12That our sons may be as plants grown up in their youth; that our daughters may be as corner stones, polished after the similitude of a palace: ▼
▼ polished: Heb. cut

verses.text_plain: That our garners may be full, affording all manner of store: that our sheep may bring forth thousands and ten thousands in our streets:
verses.verse_html:
13That our garners may be full, affording all manner of store: that our sheep may bring forth thousands and ten thousands in our streets: ▼
▼ all…: Heb. from kind to kind

footnotes.body_text: ▼ all…: Heb. from kind to kind
footnotes.body_html: ▼ all…: Heb. from kind to kind

verses.text_plain: That our oxen may be strong to labour; that there be no breaking in, nor going out; that there be no complaining in our streets.
verses.verse_html:
14That our oxen may be strong to labour; that there be no breaking in, nor going out; that there be no complaining in our streets. ▼
▼ strong…: Heb. able to bear burdens, or, loaden with flesh

footnotes.body_text: ▼ strong…: Heb. able to bear burdens, or, loaden with flesh
footnotes.body_html: ▼ strong…: Heb. able to bear burdens, or, loaden with flesh

verses.text_plain: Happy is that people, that is in such a case: yea, happy is that people, whose God is the Lord.
verses.verse_html: 15Happy is that people, that is in such a case: yea, happy is that people, whose God is the Lord.

tokens.text: that is in such a case
